.TH "drm_gtf_mode_complex" 9 "drm_gtf_mode_complex" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_gtf_mode_complex \- create the modeline based on the full GTF algorithm
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_display_mode *" drm_gtf_mode_complex
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int hdisplay "  ","
.BI "int vdisplay "  ","
.BI "int vrefresh "  ","
.BI "bool interlaced "  ","
.BI "int margins "  ","
.BI "int GTF_M "  ","
.BI "int GTF_2C "  ","
.BI "int GTF_K "  ","
.BI "int GTF_2J "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
drm device
.IP "hdisplay" 12
hdisplay size
.IP "vdisplay" 12
vdisplay size
.IP "vrefresh" 12
vrefresh rate.
.IP "interlaced" 12
whether to compute an interlaced mode
.IP "margins" 12
desired margin (borders) size
.IP "GTF_M" 12
extended GTF formula parameters
.IP "GTF_2C" 12
extended GTF formula parameters
.IP "GTF_K" 12
extended GTF formula parameters
.IP "GTF_2J" 12
extended GTF formula parameters
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
GTF feature blocks specify C and J in multiples of 0.5, so we pass them
in here multiplied by two.  For a C of 40, pass in 80.
.SH "RETURN"
The modeline based on the full GTF algorithm stored in a drm_display_mode object.
The display mode object is allocated with \fBdrm_mode_create\fP. Returns NULL
when no mode could be allocated.
